# Shared build-context ignore for BOTH images. The Dockerfiles live in infra/ but
# the build CONTEXT is this root directory (`az acr build -f infra/Dockerfile.api .`),
# so their COPY paths (compute/, agent/, web/, infra/*.requirements.txt) resolve here:
#   infra/Dockerfile      -> benefitnav-mcp (trust-core MCP server)
#   infra/Dockerfile.api  -> benefitnav-api (conductor: FastAPI + dual gate + web UI)
# Keep the cloud-build upload small and images clean.
#
# IMPORTANT: web/ is intentionally NOT excluded — the conductor image COPYs it as the
# static UI, so excluding it makes `az acr build -f infra/Dockerfile.api` fail at `COPY web/`.
# The MCP image simply doesn't COPY web/, so its presence in the context costs nothing.
.venv/
.venv-py39-backup/
**/__pycache__/
**/*.pyc
**/.DS_Store
.pytest_cache/
.git/
tests/
*.md
.env
.env.*
infra/teardown.sh
